# Cleanup — Technical Debt and Refactoring

Improve code quality through targeted refactoring. Reviewer-led: analyze before changing.

## Workflow Pipeline

```
Shipper ──► Reviewer ──► Full Stack Dev + DB Admin (parallel) ──► Shipper ──► Shipper ──► Documentor ──► Shipper
Branch       Analyze       Refactor                                Commit      Test         Update Docs     PR
```

## Steps

| # | Task | Role | Blocked By |
|---|------|------|------------|
| 1 | Create branch `refactor/<area>` from main | Shipper | — |
| 2 | Analyze code for smells, bottlenecks, and refactoring opportunities | Reviewer | 1 |
| 3 | Refactor application code based on review findings | Full Stack Dev | 2 |
| 4 | Refactor data layer based on review findings (if needed) | DB Admin | 2 |
| 5 | Commit refactoring changes (`refactor: ...`) | Shipper | 3, 4 |
| 6 | Run full test suite and validate | Shipper | 5 |
| 7 | Update documentation for refactoring changes | Documentor | 6 |
| 8 | Create PR to main with before/after summary | Shipper | 6, 7 |

## Key Points

- Steps 3 and 4 run in parallel after review completes
- Review first, refactor second — understand before changing
- PR should include a before/after summary of improvements
